{"lemma":"أُنْثَى","slug":"أُنْثَى","root":"#.ن.ث","root_slug":"_-ن-ث","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ن-ث","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أُنْثَى","root":"أنث","pos":"N","occurrence_count":24},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1315","n43830"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8F%D9%86%D9%92%D8%AB%D9%8E%D9%89"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a female","examples":[{"text":"يَا أَيُّهَا النَّاسُ إِنَّا خَلَقْنَاكُم مِن ذَكَرٍ وَأُنْثَى وَجَعَلْنَاكُمْ شُعُوبًا وَقَبَائِلَ لِتَعَارَفُوا","english":"O mankind! Indeed, We created you from a male and a female and made you nations and tribes that you may be well acquainted with one another."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"testicles"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"female","tags":["feminine"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"feminine","tags":["feminine"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ʔanθ-at-. Related to the verb أَنُثَ (ʔanuṯa, “to be feminine”). Has the form of a feminine elative. Cognate with Ugaritic 𐎀𐎘𐎚 (ảṯt, “wife”), Akkadian 𒁮 (aššatum, “wife”), Aramaic אִנְתְּתָא (ʾintəṯā), אִיתְּתָא (ʾittəṯā), Hebrew אִשָּׁה (ʾiššâ) and Classical Syriac ܐܢܬܬܐ."},"ipa":["/ʔun.θaː/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1315","headword_ar":"اُنْثَي","root":"Anv","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Female; feminine; of the female,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"feminine, sex,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gender; contr."},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akarN","text_ar":"ذَكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, S, M:) an epithet applied to anything of that sex or gender: (T:) IAar asserts, that a woman is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Anvy","text_ar":"انثي"},{"kind":"text","text":"from the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baladN A^aniyvN","text_ar":"بَلَدٌ اَنِيثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v, because of her softness; she being more soft than a man: (M, L:) [but see the observation at the end of the first paragraph of this art.:] the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inaAvN","text_ar":"اـِنَاثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, S, M, A, Msb, K;) and sometimes one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unuvN","text_ar":"اُنُثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as though it were pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inaAvN","text_ar":"اـِنَاثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) or it is [truly] pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inaAvN","text_ar":"اـِنَاثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"numurN","text_ar":"نُمُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nimaArN","text_ar":"نِمَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaAvaY","text_ar":"اَنَاثَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, A, Msb, K,) which last occurs in poetry. (T.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA TaAy^irN wa A^unovaAhu","text_ar":"هٰذَا طَايِرٌ وَ اُنْثَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is a"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bird and his female"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unovaAtuhu","text_ar":"اُنْثَاتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (ISk, T.) In the Kur iv. 117, I'Ab reads"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uvunFA","text_ar":"اُثُنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unuvFA","text_ar":"اُنُثًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inaAvFA","text_ar":"اـِنَاثًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and Fr says that it is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wavanN","text_ar":"وَثَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuvunN","text_ar":"وُثُنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uq~itatN","text_ar":"اُقِّتَتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuq~itatN","text_ar":"وُقِّتَتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T, L.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN A^anovaY","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ اَنْثَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A feminine woman,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a perfect woman;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, A, K;) a woman being thus termed in praise; like as a man is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN *akarN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ ذَكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, A.) ―         -b3-  [The pl.]"}],"source_refs":["T","S","M","L","A","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n43830","headword_ar":"اَنْثَى","root":"nvY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avonaY","text_ar":"اَثْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}